def cal_distance(one, other):
    R = 6373.0
    lat1 = radians(one[0])
    lon1 = radians(one[1])
    lat2 = radians(other[0])
    lon2 = radians(other[1])
    dlon = lon2 - lon1
    dlat = lat2 - lat1
    a = sin(dlat / 2)**2 + cos(lat1) * cos(lat2) * sin(dlon / 2)**2
    c = 2 * atan2(sqrt(a), sqrt(1 - a))
    distance = R * c
    return distance

def is_valid(text):
    cnt = 0
    stack = []
    for char in text:
        if char == "[":
            stack.append(char)
        elif char == "]":
            if len(stack) == 0:
                return False
            stack.pop()
    return len(stack) == 0


def make_list(text):
    if not is_valid(text):
        return "INVALID"

    ret = []
    i = 0
    temp = ""
    while i < len(text):
        if text[i] == ",":
            ret.append(temp)
            temp = ""
        elif text[i] == "[":
            cnt = 1
            start = i
            end = i
            while cnt > 0:
                i += 1
                if text[i] == "[":
                    cnt += 1
                elif text[i] == "]":
                    cnt -= 1
                end = i
            i += 1
            ret.append(make_list(text[(start+1):end]))

        else:
            temp += temp.join(text[i])

        i += 1

        if i == len(text) and temp != "":
            ret.append(temp)

    return ret

def getAddressDict(address):
    raw_data = getAddressInfo(address)["result"]
    ret = {}
    
    name = ""
    address = ""
    x = ""
    y = ""

    if "site" in raw_data:
        data = raw_data["site"]["list"][0]
        ret["name"] = data["name"]
        ret["address"] = data["address"]
        ret["longitude"] = data["x"]
        ret["latitude"] = data["y"]

    else:
        data = raw_data["address"]["list"][0]
        ret["name"] = data["name"]
        ret["address"] = data["fullAddress"]
        ret["longitude"] = data["x"]
        ret["latitude"] = data["y"]
        
    return ret

from pyproj import Proj, transform

def InnerToLatLng(InnerXY):
    proj_UTMK = Proj(init='epsg:5179')
    proj_WGS84 = Proj(init='epsg:4326')
    InnerXY[0] = (InnerXY[0]-34e7)/10
    InnerXY[1] = (InnerXY[1]-13e7)/10
    latLng = transform(proj_UTMK, proj_WGS84, InnerXY[0], InnerXY[1])
    return [latLng[0], latLng[1]]

def get_line(point, path, past_circle, m):
    path.append((point[0],point[1]))
    present_circle = point
    if len(past_circle) > 0:
        locations = [past_circle, present_circle]
    return present_circle

def visualize_step(step, path, past_circle, m, isLatLng = True):
    pathPoints = step["path"].split(" ")
    for pathPoint in pathPoints:
        if len(pathPoint) == 0:
            continue
        pathPoint = pathPoint.split(",")
        pathPoint = list(map(float, pathPoint))
        if isLatLng == False:
            pathPoint = InnerToLatLng(pathPoint)
        pathPoint.reverse()
        past_circle = get_line(pathPoint, path, past_circle, m)

def visualizeExpectedRouteByCar(start, dest, m):
    [startLat, startLng] = start
    [destLat, destLng] = dest
    
    url = "https://m.map.naver.com/spirra/findCarRoute.nhn?route=route3&output=json&result=web3&coord_type=latlng&search=2&car=0&mileage=12.4&start=" + startLng + "%2C" + startLat + "&destination=" + destLng + "%2C" + destLat
    headers = {"user-agent" : "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/67.0.3396.99 Safari/537.36"}
    resp = requests.get(url=url, headers=headers)
    full_steps = json.loads(resp.text)["routes"][0]["legs"]

    for steps in full_steps:
        steps = steps["steps"]
        path = []
        past_circle = []
        for step in steps:
            visualize_step(step, path, past_circle, m)
            if "steps" in step:
                for detail_step in step["steps"]:
                    visualize_step(detail_step, path, past_circle, m)

        if len(path) > 0:
            folium.PolyLine(path, color="#00498c",weight=3.5,opacity=0.7).add_to(m)

def getVisitTimeline(location_data, point, distance):
    geo_data = location_data.copy()
    geo_data['distance'] = geo_data.apply(lambda row:cal_distance([float(row['latitude']), float(row['longitude'])], point), axis = 1)
    geo_data = geo_data[geo_data.distance < distance]
    return geo_data

def visualizeVisitTimeline(location_data, target, distance, color='blue',fig=None):
    geoLocation = getAddressDict(target)
    point = list(map(float, [geoLocation["latitude"], geoLocation["longitude"]]))
    visit_data = getVisitTimeline(location_data, point, distance)
    visit_data = visit_data[(visit_data.datetime > '2019-08-01') & (visit_data.datetime < '2019-08-10') ]
    tz_float = mdates.date2num(datetime.datetime(2019,1,1,tzinfo=datetime.timezone(datetime.timedelta(hours=9)))) % 1
    date = (mdates.date2num(visit_data['datetime']) - tz_float).astype(int) + 1
    time = []
    if len(date) > 0:
        time = ((mdates.date2num(visit_data['datetime']) - tz_float) % 1) + int(date[0] - tz_float)
    if fig == None:
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9,9))
        ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
        ax.yaxis_date('Asia/Seoul')
        ax.xaxis_date('Asia/Seoul')
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(DayLocator())
        ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%m-%d'))
        ax.yaxis.set_major_locator(HourLocator())
        ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%H:%M:%S'))
        ax.set_ylim(int(date[0] - tz_float), int(date[0] - tz_float) + 1)
    else:
        ax = fig.get_axes()[0]

    ax.plot_date(date, time, c=color, marker='.')
    return fig

def stripTag(text):
  while text.find('<') != -1:
    start = text.find('<')
    end = text.find('>')
    text = text[:start] + text[(end+1):]
  return text

def timeToDatetime(line):
    [date, time_standard] = line.split(" ")
    [year, month, day] = date.split(" ")
    if len(month) == 2:
        month = "0" + month
    if len(day) == 2:
        day = "0" + day
    date = year + " " + month + " " + day
    [noon, time, standard] = time_standard.split(" ")
    if noon.find("") != -1:
        [hour, min, sec] = time.split(":")
        if hour != "12":
            hour = str(int(hour) + 12)
        time = hour + ":" + min + ":" + sec
    else:
        [hour, min, sec] = time.split(":")
        if len(hour) == 1:
            hour = "0" + hour
        if hour == "12":
            hour = "00"
        time = hour + ":" + min + ":" + sec
    ret = datetime.datetime.strptime(date + " " + time + " " + standard, "%Y. %m. %d. %H:%M:%S %Z") + datetime.timedelta(hours=9)
    return ret

    date_time = timeToDatetime(time).replace(tzinfo=datetime.timezone(datetime.timedelta(hours=9)))

def getAppUseData(appTotalData, app):
    return appTotalData[appTotalData.activity.str.contains(app)]

def visualizeAppUseTimeline(appTotalData, app, color='blue', marker ='.', mfc='None', fig=None):
    appUseData = getAppUseData(appTotalData, app)
    appUseData = appUseData[ (appUseData.datetime > '2018-11-12') & (appUseData.datetime < '2018-11-18') ]
    tz_float = mdates.date2num(datetime.datetime(2019,1,1,tzinfo=datetime.timezone(datetime.timedelta(hours=9)))) % 1
    date = (mdates.date2num(appUseData['datetime']) - tz_float).astype(int) + 1
    time = []
    if len(date) > 0:
        time = ((mdates.date2num(appUseData['datetime']) - tz_float) % 1) + 1
    if fig == None:
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9,9))
        ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
        ax.yaxis_date('Asia/Seoul')
        ax.xaxis_date('Asia/Seoul')
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(DayLocator())
        ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%m-%d'))
        ax.yaxis.set_major_locator(HourLocator())
        ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%H:%M:%S'))
        ax.set_ylim(1,2)
    else:
        ax = fig.get_axes()[0]
    ax.plot_date(date, time, c=color, marker=marker, markersize=9, mfc=mfc)
    return fig

def shortenKeyword(text):
    if len(text) > 12:
        text = text[:10] + "..."
    return text

def visualizeKeywordTimeline(search_df, fig=None):
    searchData = search_df[ (search_df.datetime > '2019-06-15') & (search_df.datetime < '2019-06-20') ]
    tz_float = mdates.date2num(datetime.datetime(2019,1,1,tzinfo=datetime.timezone(datetime.timedelta(hours=9)))) % 1
    date = (mdates.date2num(searchData['datetime']) - tz_float).astype(int) + 1
    time = []
    if len(date) > 0:
        time = ((mdates.date2num(searchData['datetime']) - tz_float) % 1) + 1
    if fig == None:
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))
        ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
        ax.yaxis_date('Asia/Seoul')
        ax.xaxis_date('Asia/Seoul')
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(DayLocator())
        ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%m-%d'))
        ax.yaxis.set_major_locator(HourLocator())
        ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%H:%M:%S'))
        ax.set_ylim(1.4, 1.9)
    else:
        ax = fig.get_axes()[0]
        
    ax.plot_date(date, time, color='white')
    searchData.loc[:,'activity'] = searchData.activity.apply(shortenKeyword)
    plt.grid()
    for i in range(len(date)):
        plt.text(date[i] - 0.2, time[i], searchData.activity.iloc[i], fontsize=12)
    return fig
